  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\n[q,p]=i\\hbar .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nContinuous-variable quantum systems use observables with continuous spectra, such as position $q$ and momentum $p$.\n\nThe commutator is defined by\n\\begin{equation}\n[q,p]=qp-pq .\n\\end{equation}\n\nCanonical quantization imposes\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n[q,p]=i\\hbar .\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\nIn the Trawinistic extension, curvature may modify the phase-space volume element while preserving the canonical commutator as the primary algebraic witness.\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nContinuous-variable systems extend the registry from finite qubit states into infinite-dimensional Hilbert-space dynamics.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
